The CARDAMOM Rh dataset is used in the main manuscript for the following two main reasons: firstly, we calculate τs using heterotrophic respiration which allows for consistency between models and observations, and secondly, the dataset does not use a prescribed q10 sensitivity21. Instead, the CARDAMOM Rh dataset was derived by explicitly assimilating observations into a process-based diagnostic land-surface model. To test the robustness of our results, we also repeated our analysis with MODIS NPP and Raich 2002, for both CMIP6 and CMIP5 together, and as separate model ensembles. Supplementary Fig. 6 shows the observational \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
